# .trivyignore
# Use this file to manage vulnerability, misconfiguration, and secret scanning exclusions.
# Each line can be a CVE ID, misconfiguration ID (e.g., DS-0002), or secret rule ID.

# DS-0002: Specify at least 1 USER command in Dockerfile with non-root user as argument
# Running containers with 'root' user is flagged by Trivy as a HIGH misconfiguration.
# We ignore this for ephemeral testing images (like Dockerfile.karate) and local dev environments.
DS-0002
